menu "Board Common"

    config BOARD_LANDSCAPE
        bool "Landscape orientation"
        default n
        help
            Rotate the display 90 degrees for landscape orientation.

            When enabled, LVGL sees swapped dimensions (V_RES x H_RES)
            and the board init code applies the appropriate flush callback
            rotation and touch coordinate transforms.

            The convenience macros BOARD_DISP_H_RES / BOARD_DISP_V_RES
            reflect the logical (post-rotation) dimensions.

endmenu
